<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1437,1299,1830]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1696,1722]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species first branched off in the 
<taxonomicName box="[749,833,1696,1722]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tanabei">
<emphasis box="[749,833,1696,1722]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">tanabei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup (
<figureCitation box="[962,1029,1695,1722]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1683,1708]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,779,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,777,1658]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1. The strict consensus tree resulting from the parsimony analysis I (PAUP* v4.0a166) of the data matrix of 40 spp. × 66 morphological characters (Appendix 1) for the genus Phortica (especially focusing on the subgenus Ashima). Synapomorphies (solid circle: nonhomoplastic; open circle: homoplastic) inferred from both ACCTRAN and DELTRAN character optimization are indicated on each internal branch along with support values (bootstrap frequency %)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884614" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884614/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The remaining three species form a cluster (BP = 82%) with two synapomorphies (
<figureCitation box="[704,771,1731,1758]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1683,1708]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,779,1658]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,777,1658]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1. The strict consensus tree resulting from the parsimony analysis I (PAUP* v4.0a166) of the data matrix of 40 spp. × 66 morphological characters (Appendix 1) for the genus Phortica (especially focusing on the subgenus Ashima). Synapomorphies (solid circle: nonhomoplastic; open circle: homoplastic) inferred from both ACCTRAN and DELTRAN character optimization are indicated on each internal branch along with support values (bootstrap frequency %)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884614" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884614/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
): dorsomedial, tentorial apodeme ≥ 2/3 basal, parallel por- tion of dorsolateral, tentorial apodeme (ch.1-0; 
<figureCitation box="[682,771,1767,1794]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1911,1936]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[215,1372,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 7. Phortica (Ashima) akutsui Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype). A, Head (caudal view); B, frons; C, antenna; D, abdominal sternites; E, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); F, postgonites (anteroventral view); G, H, phallic organs (lateral and ventral views, respectively). Abbreviations: dl t a, dorsolateral, tentorial apodeme; pocl s, postocular setae. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B, C, E–H; 0.5 mm in A, D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884628/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
); and setae on and/or near ventral margin of epandrium not longer than others (ch.33-0; 
<figureCitation box="[469,561,1803,1829]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1435,417,1882]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 6. Phortica (Ashima) halimunensis Toda, sp. nov. (A–G; ♂ paratype) and Phortica (Ashima) longipenis Chen &amp; Wen, 2005 (H; ♂ paratype). A, Antenna; B, prementum; C, abdominal sternites; D, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); E, phal- lic organs (lateral view); F, aedeagal sheath and aedeagal median rod (ventral view); G, hypandrium, pregonites and aedeagus (ventral view); H, aedeagus and aedeagal sheath (A-type; ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in A, B, D–H; 0.5 mm in C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884626" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884626/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Figs 6D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[573,607,1804,1830]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1911,1936]" captionTargetBox="[215,1371,181,1885]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[215,1372,181,1885]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 7. Phortica (Ashima) akutsui Toda, sp. nov. (♂ holotype). A, Head (caudal view); B, frons; C, antenna; D, abdominal sternites; E, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); F, postgonites (anteroventral view); G, H, phallic organs (lateral and ventral views, respectively). Abbreviations: dl t a, dorsolateral, tentorial apodeme; pocl s, postocular setae. Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B, C, E–H; 0.5 mm in A, D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884628" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884628/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">7E</figureCitation>
